    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "258ccaa6_fc6ecef0",
        "filename": "go/swarming/autoscaler/testutils.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-30T20:10:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: I think URLMock is good for unit testing code that directly calls those URLs. When mocking calls several layers down, it can be difficult to debug the tests and difficult to maintain (e.g. if the API changes). If there is a convenient place to use an interface and mock the interface, I think that would make the tests easier to maintain.",
      "revId": "08fcdb6fdd1e4fd30b4db1db3900b3db281fa6ba",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "cf574d9f_c93537a2",
        "filename": "go/swarming/autoscaler/testutils.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-31T19:07:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree that it\u0027s more straightforward to mock out interfaces for testing but in most cases I prefer to test the whole stack by mocking at the HTTP request level.  It gives you more realistic behavior and better control over mocking actual API behavior, rather than just assuming everything below the interface will behave like the test expects.",
      "parentUuid": "258ccaa6_fc6ecef0",
      "revId": "08fcdb6fdd1e4fd30b4db1db3900b3db281fa6ba",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
